From: Thomas Gleixner <tglx@linutronix.de>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2009 08:44:27 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 202/349] fs: namespace preemption fix
Origin: https://www.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/projects/rt/4.9/older/patches-4.9.115-rt93.tar.xz

On RT we cannot loop with preemption disabled here as
mnt_make_readonly() might have been preempted. We can safely enable
preemption while waiting for MNT_WRITE_HOLD to be cleared. Safe on !RT
as well.

Signed-off-by: Thomas Gleixner <tglx@linutronix.de>
---
 fs/namespace.c | 5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/fs/namespace.c b/fs/namespace.c
index 6c873b330a93..b7b2289ada3f 100644
--- a/fs/namespace.c
+++ b/fs/namespace.c
@@ -357,8 +357,11 @@ int __mnt_want_write(struct vfsmount *m)
 	 * incremented count after it has set MNT_WRITE_HOLD.
 	 */
 	smp_mb();
-	while (ACCESS_ONCE(mnt->mnt.mnt_flags) & MNT_WRITE_HOLD)
+	while (ACCESS_ONCE(mnt->mnt.mnt_flags) & MNT_WRITE_HOLD) {
+		preempt_enable();
 		cpu_relax();
+		preempt_disable();
+	}
 	/*
 	 * After the slowpath clears MNT_WRITE_HOLD, mnt_is_readonly will
 	 * be set to match its requirements. So we must not load that until
